            "content": "# Split process_message from tombstone — Implementation Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Split `process_message` into a sync local phase and an async tombstone phase so incoming messages display immediately without waiting for tombstone network I/O.\n\n**Architecture:** Extract the decrypt+store+DAG logic into `process_message_local()` (sync), the tombstone into `send_tombstone()` (async). The existing `process_message` becomes a wrapper. The TUI drainers call the split API: notify UI after local processing, fire-and-forget the tombstone.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Rust, tokio::spawn\n\n**Spec:** `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-03-27-split-process-message-from-tombstone.md`\n\n---\n\n## File Map\n\n| File | Action | Responsibility |\n|------|--------|---------------|\n| `crates/reme-core/src/lib.rs` | Modify | Add `ProcessedMessage`, `process_message_local`, `send_tombstone`; refactor `process_message` as wrapper |\n| `apps/client/src/tui/app.rs` | Modify | Update drainers in `spawn_background_tasks` to use split API |\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: Add ProcessedMessage struct and split process_message in reme-core\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `crates/reme-core/src/lib.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add `ProcessedMessage` struct**\n\nAfter `ReceivedMessage` (around line 93), add:\n\n```rust\n/// Result of local message processing (decrypt + store + DAG).\n/// Contains the decrypted message for display and an optional tombstone to send.\npub struct ProcessedMessage {\n    /// The decrypted message ready for display\n    pub received: ReceivedMessage,\n    /// Tombstone to fire-and-forget (None for detached messages)\n    pub pending_tombstone: Option<SignedAckTombstone>,\n}\n```\n\nEnsure `SignedAckTombstone` is re-exported or accessible. Check the existing imports — it's from `reme_message`. It should already be in scope. If not, add the import.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Create `process_message_local` method**\n\nAdd a new method to `impl<T: Transport> Client<T>` (the generic impl block, NOT the `TransportCoordinator` one — this method doesn't use transport). The method contains ALL the logic from the current `process_message` EXCEPT the tombstone send (lines 712-742).\n\n```rust\n/// Process an incoming envelope locally: decrypt, verify, store, update DAG.\n///\n/// This performs all local operations (crypto, storage, DAG tracking) without\n/// any network I/O. The caller is responsible for sending the tombstone\n/// returned in `ProcessedMessage::pending_tombstone`.\n///\n/// This split allows UIs to display the message immediately while the\n/// tombstone send happens asynchronously (fire-and-forget).\npub fn process_message_local(\n    &self,\n    outer: &OuterEnvelope,\n) -> Result<ProcessedMessage, ClientError> {\n```\n\nCopy the body of `process_message` from line 638 (routing key check) through to the end (line 876, `Ok(ReceivedMessage { ... })`), but:\n\n1. **Remove** the tombstone send block (lines 712-742: the `if should_tombstone { ... submit_ack_tombstone ... }` block)\n2. **Instead**, build the tombstone and include it in the return value:\n\n```rust\n    // Build tombstone for caller to send asynchronously (fire-and-forget)\n    let pending_tombstone = if should_tombstone {\n        Some(SignedAckTombstone::new(\n            outer.message_id,\n            ack_secret,\n            &self.private_key(),\n        ))\n    } else {\n        None\n    };\n```\n\n3. **Return** `ProcessedMessage` instead of `ReceivedMessage`:\n\n```rust\n    Ok(ProcessedMessage {\n        received: ReceivedMessage {\n            message_id: outer.message_id,\n            from: inner.from,\n            content: inner.content,\n            created_at_ms: inner.created_at_ms,\n            content_id,\n            has_gaps,\n            sender_state_reset,\n            local_state_behind,\n        },\n        pending_tombstone,\n    })\n```\n\nNote: this method is NOT async — remove the `async` keyword. All operations inside are synchronous (crypto + SQLite).\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Create `send_tombstone` method**\n\nAdd to the same generic `impl<T: Transport> Client<T>` block:\n\n```rust\n/// Send an auto-tombstone for a processed message (fire-and-forget).\n///\n/// On success, removes the stored `pending_ack`. On failure, logs a warning —\n/// the `ack_secret` remains stored for retry via `acknowledge_received()`.\npub async fn send_tombstone(\n    &self,\n    message_id: MessageID,\n    tombstone: SignedAckTombstone,\n) -> Result<(), ClientError> {\n    self.transport\n        .submit_ack_tombstone(tombstone)\n        .await\n        .map_err(ClientError::Transport)?;\n\n    // Tombstone succeeded — remove stored ack_secret (no longer needed)\n    if let Err(e) = self.storage.remove_pending_ack(&message_id) {\n        warn!(\n            message_id = ?message_id,\n            error = %e,\n            \"Failed to remove pending_ack after successful tombstone\"\n        );\n    }\n    debug!(message_id = ?message_id, \"Auto-tombstone sent successfully\");\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\nCheck the error conversion — `submit_ack_tombstone` returns a `TransportError`. Verify `ClientError::Transport` exists or use the appropriate variant. Read the `ClientError` enum to find the right variant.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Refactor `process_message` as a wrapper**\n\nReplace the entire body of the existing `process_message` with:\n\n```rust\npub async fn process_message(\n    &self,\n    outer: &OuterEnvelope,\n) -> Result<ReceivedMessage, ClientError> {\n    let processed = self.process_message_local(outer)?;\n    if let Some(tombstone) = processed.pending_tombstone {\n        // Inline tombstone send (original behavior: block until sent)\n        // Callers that want fire-and-forget should use process_message_local + send_tombstone\n        if let Err(e) = self.send_tombstone(outer.message_id, tombstone).await {\n            warn!(\n                message_id = ?outer.message_id,\n                error = %e,\n                \"Failed to send auto-tombstone (ack_secret stored for retry)\"\n            );\n        }\n    }\n    Ok(processed.received)\n}\n```\n\nNote: the old `process_message` treated tombstone failure as non-fatal (logged warning, didn't return error). The wrapper preserves this behavior.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Verify it compiles and tests pass**\n\nRun: `cargo check -p reme-core && cargo test -p reme-core`\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/reme-core/src/lib.rs\ngit commit -m \"refactor(core): split process_message into local + tombstone phases\n\nAdd process_message_local() (sync: decrypt, store, DAG) and\nsend_tombstone() (async: network I/O). The existing process_message\nbecomes a wrapper for backward compatibility.\n\nThis enables UIs to display messages immediately while tombstone\nsend happens asynchronously.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: Update TUI drainers to use the split API\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/tui/app.rs` (`spawn_background_tasks` method)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Update coordinator event drainer**\n\nIn `spawn_background_tasks`, replace the coordinator drainer (lines ~887-901):\n\n```rust\n// --- Coordinator event drainer ---\nlet client = self.client.clone();\nlet tx = self.action_tx.clone();\nlet mut coordinator_events =\n    std::mem::replace(&mut self.coordinator_events, mpsc::unbounded_channel().1);\ntokio::spawn(async move {\n    while let Some(event) = coordinator_events.recv().await {\n        if let TransportEvent::Message(envelope) = event {\n            match client.process_message_local(&envelope) {\n                Ok(processed) => {\n                    // Notify UI immediately — message is decrypted and stored\n                    if tx\n                        .send(Action::MessageProcessed {\n                            result: Ok(processed.received),\n                            source: MessageSource::Coordinator,\n                        })\n                        .is_err()\n                    {\n                        break;\n                    }\n                    // Fire-and-forget tombstone\n                    if let Some(tombstone) = processed.pending_tombstone {\n                        let client = client.clone();\n                        let msg_id = envelope.message_id;\n                        tokio::spawn(async move {\n                            if let Err(e) = client.send_tombstone(msg_id, tombstone).await {\n                                warn!(\n                                    message_id = ?msg_id,\n                                    error = %e,\n                                    \"Tombstone send failed\"\n                                );\n                            }\n                        });\n                    }\n                }\n                Err(e) => {\n                    if tx\n                        .send(Action::MessageProcessed {\n                            result: Err(e.to_string()),\n                            source: MessageSource::Coordinator,\n                        })\n                        .is_err()\n                    {\n                        break;\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n});\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Update node event drainer**\n\nSame pattern for the node event drainer (lines ~905-932):\n\n```rust\n// --- Node event drainer ---\nif let Some(mut node_rx) = self.node_event_rx.take() {\n    let client = self.client.clone();\n    let tx = self.action_tx.clone();\n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        while let Some(event) = node_rx.recv().await {\n            match event {\n                NodeEvent::MessageReceived(envelope) => {\n                    debug!(\"Received message from embedded node\");\n                    match client.process_message_local(&envelope) {\n                        Ok(processed) => {\n                            if tx\n                                .send(Action::MessageProcessed {\n                                    result: Ok(processed.received),\n                                    source: MessageSource::EmbeddedNode,\n                                })\n                                .is_err()\n                            {\n                                break;\n                            }\n                            if let Some(tombstone) = processed.pending_tombstone {\n                                let client = client.clone();\n                                let msg_id = envelope.message_id;\n                                tokio::spawn(async move {\n                                    if let Err(e) =\n                                        client.send_tombstone(msg_id, tombstone).await\n                                    {\n                                        warn!(\n                                            message_id = ?msg_id,\n                                            error = %e,\n                                            \"Tombstone send failed\"\n                                        );\n                                    }\n                                });\n                            }\n                        }\n                        Err(e) => {\n                            if tx\n                                .send(Action::MessageProcessed {\n                                    result: Err(e.to_string()),\n                                    source: MessageSource::EmbeddedNode,\n                                })\n                                .is_err()\n                            {\n                                break;\n                            }\n                        }\n                    }\n                }\n                NodeEvent::Error(e) => {\n                    tracing::error!(\"Embedded node error: {}\", e);\n                    if tx.send(Action::NodeError(e)).is_err() {\n                        break;\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    });\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Verify it compiles**\n\nRun: `cargo check -p client && cargo clippy -p client`\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run full workspace tests**\n\nRun: `cargo test --workspace`\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add apps/client/src/tui/app.rs\ngit commit -m \"fix(tui): display incoming messages before tombstone send\n\nUpdate background drainers to use process_message_local() for\nimmediate UI notification, then fire-and-forget the tombstone.\nMessages now appear instantly instead of waiting 2-5s for tombstone\nnetwork I/O.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\"\n```\n",
